Write a program that takes in a line of text as input, and outputs that line of text in reverse. 
The program repeats, ending when the user enters "Done", "done", or "d" for the line of text.

Ex: If the input is:

Hello there
Hey
done

then the output is:
ereht olleH
yeH


Program:
I prefer this program because this one is simplier and takes less lines and does the same work.

METHOD 1:
text = input()

while text != "Done" and text != "done" and text != "d":
    reversed_text = text[::-1]
    print(reversed_text)
    text = input()



